      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The originalist approach is indeed the most faithful way to interpret the Constitution because it anchors legal reasoning in the text and historical intent of the Founders. By treating the Constitution as a living document, judges risk injecting their own political preferences rather than adhering to the original meaning. This ensures that the Second Amendment remains a stable, text-based right rather than a shifting political tool.",
      "source": "target",
